We visited Moon Cheese for my son‚Äôs birthday before attending a NYCFC game. We had the BEST time! They were able to accommodate a party of 11 with no problems. The food was absolutely amazing! We had Tatiana as our server and she was wonderful! She was very knowledgeable about the food and gave great suggestions! Tatiana heard it was our son‚Äôs birthday and she made it extra special with a bubble machine as we sang Happy Birthday. My family thoroughly enjoyed our experience and can‚Äôt wait to go back! This is a must try restaurant!

We came here when our flight was cancelled. Emily (the owner) took care of our group of 5 and provided exceptional service and lunch for us. The place had a great vibe and was decorated with fun art. There was board and card games for the kids to play to kill time and the food was insanely good!!

The service was immaculate. Ana did a fantastic job at giving us a great experience. It was our first time here and she was attentive, kind, and fun! At the end she let us spin the wheel to win a prize and I got a free soda, but I was a little bummed because I wanted to win a free shot, but she gave me it anyways! Not just the service, but the food was actually really good. It is a lowkey place, but with great food with great portions for a fair price. The drinks were definitely potent as well. We ordered the arepas for 2 that came with nachos, colombian hot dog, premium steak fries that came with a fire show, sangria, and a modelo. Everything was so filling that I had to take most of the food to go. I would recommend this place to everyone!!

I‚Äôm REALLY torn on this place. The waitress we had did a few things that were a bit out of line, and kind of offensive.

You can see on the receipt in the photos that she wrote that the tip wasn‚Äôt included in the total. I‚Äôm not sure why it was necessary to say that. That‚Äôs to be expected, and we had every intention to tip. Me and my significant other were both a little taken aback by that, and a little offended. Was there some sort of assumption we weren‚Äôt going to tip?

Not only that, she gave us the 12‚Äù pizza and not the 16‚Äù pizza we ordered, even after we confirmed and pointed at it multiple times on the menu. We also asked for tap water, not bottled. She just said ‚ÄúNo.‚Äù She didn‚Äôt give any explanation. The bottled water cost us more than what they charge for their fruit juices. We would have gotten some other drink if we had known we would have been charged for bottled water anyway.

Needless to say, we felt a bit disrespected, and weren‚Äôt terribly happy with how the waitress treated us. Now‚Ä¶ the reason I‚Äôm so torn about this place is because the man behind the bar when we arrived (assuming the owner?) was so warm and welcoming. He even thanked us many times on our way out. Also, the food here is GREAT. We absolutely loved the Hawaiian burger.

I‚Äôd love to give this place a 5 star rating, but that waitress‚Äô service really impacted the experience for us‚Ä¶
